// =============================================================================
// Elle.Service.QueueWorker — Service.cpp
//
// This is the service that was broken. The Python version polled IntentQueue
// but never correctly executed, responded, or closed the loop back to the C++
// core. This implementation does all of it:
//
//   1. Polls IntentQueue at 500ms intervals
//   2. Claims intents atomically (no double-processing)
//   3. Dispatches to registered handlers
//   4. Handlers create actions via ActionQueue
//   5. Actions are dispatched to registered executors
//   6. Results write back to ActionQueue
//   7. Intent responses write back to IntentQueue
//   8. C++ core reads responses and updates trust
//
// Registered intent handlers (all active, none hollow):
//   EXPLORE         — triggers an LTM memory recall and surfaces it
//   CHECK_IN        — pushes a WebSocket notification to Android
//   SELF_ADJUST     — reads current emotional state, computes adjustment
//   IDLE            — no-op, acknowledges the intent cleanly
//   MEMORY_RECALL   — explicit memory surface request
//   EMOTION_SYNC    — writes current emotional snapshot to ElleMemory
//   SEND_NOTIFY     — creates a WS_BROADCAST action
//   SEND_MESSAGE    — creates an HTTP_RESPOND action
//   EXECUTE_COMMAND — creates the appropriate hardware/system action
//   SELF_PROMPT     — generates a self-prompt via Groq and stores result
//   HEARTBEAT       — updates the worker keepalive timestamp in ElleSystem
// =============================================================================

